Social media users were up in arms on Tuesday following Atul Gupta's interview with the UK's BBC Radio 4 on his family's alleged role in state capture.  Atul Gupta also denied perpetuating the ideology of white monopoly capital through the services of British PR firm, Bell Pottinger. He said he did not know where the white monopoly capital narrative comes from, and that the claims against the family with regards to state capture had no authenticity.  Listen to the full interview. -- South Africans took to Twitter to voice how they felt about Atul's point blank denials.           